works.description: Introduced recently at the Seoul Motor Show, the Chevrolet Mi-ray Concept aims to offer a fresh look at what sports cars of the future might be. The Mi-ray hybrid roadster was developed at the GM Advanced Design Studio in Seoul. The Mi-ray (Korean for ‘future’), which celebrates brand’s 100-year design heritage, combines superior hybrid propulsion technology and advanced styling. The Mi-ray is small and open like the 1963 Monza SS, and light and purposeful like the 1962 Corvair Super Spyder. Its aerodynamic fuselage is evocative of today’s jet fighters.
